# LeafScan — Plant Disease Detection System

AI-powered plant disease detection using EfficientNet-B0 transfer learning on the PlantVillage dataset (38 classes, ~54k images).

---

## Architecture Overview

```
plant-disease-detection/
├── model/
│   ├── train.py              # Training pipeline (EfficientNet-B0, AMP, cosine LR)
│   ├── evaluate.py           # Evaluation: confusion matrix, per-class accuracy, history plots
│   ├── gradcam.py            # Grad-CAM visualization using PyTorch hooks
│   ├── class_names.json      # 38 PlantVillage class labels
│   └── saved/                # Saved model artifacts (after training)
│       ├── plant_disease_model.pt
│       ├── class_names.json
│       └── history.json
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py               # FastAPI application, API routes, static file serving
│   ├── inference.py          # Model loading, preprocessing, prediction
│   ├── recommendations.py    # Disease recommendation engine (38 classes, full detail)
│   ├── marketplace.py        # Mock product catalog and disease-to-product mapping
│   └── requirements.txt      # Backend Python dependencies
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html            # Single-page application
│   ├── styles.css            # Dark botanical theme, glassmorphism, responsive
│   └── app.js                # Drag-drop upload, API calls, result rendering
├── data/
│   └── README.md             # Dataset download instructions
└── requirements.txt          # Training dependencies
```

---

## Model Architecture

- **Base model**: EfficientNet-B0 (ImageNet pretrained via torchvision)
- **Strategy**: Two-phase fine-tuning
  - Phase 1 (epochs 1–10): Freeze backbone, train custom head only
  - Phase 2 (epochs 11–30): Unfreeze full model with lower learning rate
- **Custom head**: `Dropout(0.4) → Linear(1280→512) → SiLU → Dropout(0.3) → Linear(512→38)`
- **Training**: AdamW + CosineAnnealingLR + Mixed Precision (AMP) + Label Smoothing
- **Augmentation**: RandomResizedCrop, Flips, Rotation, ColorJitter, RandomGrayscale
- **Input size**: 224×224

---

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone and create environment

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd plant-disease-detection
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate          # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 2. Download dataset

```bash
pip install kaggle
# Place your kaggle.json API key in ~/.kaggle/
kaggle datasets download -d mohitsingh1804/plantvillage -p ./data
unzip ./data/plantvillage.zip -d ./data/
```

### 3. Train the model

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
cd model
DATA_DIR=../data/PlantVillage MODEL_DIR=./saved python train.py
```

Training with a GPU (RTX 3080+) takes approximately 30–60 minutes for 30 epochs.
On CPU, reduce epochs in `train.py` or use a smaller batch size.

### 4. Evaluate the model (optional)

```bash
DATA_DIR=../data/PlantVillage MODEL_PATH=./saved/plant_disease_model.pt OUTPUT_DIR=./evaluation python evaluate.py
```

This generates:
- `confusion_matrix.png`
- `training_history.png`
- `per_class_accuracy.png`
- `classification_report.txt`

### 5. Start the backend

```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
# API running at http://localhost:8000
# Swagger UI at http://localhost:8000/docs
```

The backend automatically serves the frontend at `http://localhost:8000`.

### 6. (Optional) Standalone frontend

Open `frontend/index.html` directly in a browser while the backend is running.

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/` | Serves the web application |
| `GET` | `/health` | Health check |
| `POST` | `/api/predict` | Predict disease from uploaded image |
| `GET` | `/api/products` | List all marketplace products |
| `GET` | `/api/products/{id}` | Get single product |
| `GET` | `/api/classes` | List all 38 class names |

### Predict endpoint

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/predict \
  -F "file=@leaf.jpg" \
  -F "gradcam=true"
```

Response:
```json
{
  "prediction": {
    "plant": "Tomato",
    "disease": "Late blight",
    "is_healthy": false,
    "confidence": 0.9342,
    "raw_class": "Tomato___Late_blight",
    "top5": [...]
  },
  "recommendation": {
    "description": "...",
    "causes": [...],
    "treatment": [...],
    "prevention": [...],
    "severity": "critical"
  },
  "products": [...],
  "images": {
    "original": "data:image/jpeg;base64,...",
    "gradcam": "data:image/jpeg;base64,..."
  }
}
```

---

## Demo Mode

If no trained model is found at the expected path, the backend runs in **demo mode** — returning a random prediction with simulated confidence values. This allows testing the full UI without a trained model.

The frontend displays a warning banner when demo mode is active.

---

## Features

- **38-class classification** across 14 crop species
- **Transfer learning** with two-phase fine-tuning strategy
- **Grad-CAM** heat map visualization showing model attention regions
- **Full recommendation engine** with description, causes, treatment, and prevention for all 38 classes
- **Mock marketplace** with 15 products, disease-to-product mapping, and category filtering
- **Dark botanical UI** with drag-drop upload, confidence visualization, and top-5 predictions
- **Responsive design** — mobile-friendly layout

---

## Performance Expectations

Typical performance on PlantVillage test set:

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Test Accuracy | ~96–98% |
| Top-5 Accuracy | ~99.5%+ |
| Inference time (GPU) | ~15ms |
| Inference time (CPU) | ~150–400ms |

